
# Wazuh SIEM/XDR Home Lab Project Summary

## Project Overview

Deployed a fully functional Wazuh SIEM/XDR home lab environment using an Ubuntu virtual machine as the central server and a macOS endpoint as the monitored agent. The project demonstrates end-to-end security monitoring capabilities, including installation, configuration, troubleshooting, and alert validation through File Integrity Monitoring (FIM).

--

## Technical Implementation

### 1. Wazuh Server Installation (Ubuntu 24.04 LTS)

**System Update:**

```bash
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
```

**Download and Run Wazuh Installer:**

```bash
curl -sO https://packages.wazuh.com/4.7/wazuh-install.sh
sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a
```

The `-a` flag automates the installation, setting up all required components: Wazuh Manager, Filebeat, Indexer, and Wazuh Dashboard.

For Ubuntu 24.04 (newer than officially supported versions), the OS check was bypassed using `-i`:

```bash
sudo bash wazuh-install.sh -a -i
```

**Successful Installation Output:**

```text
Wazuh indexer installation finished.
wazuh-indexer service started.
Wazuh manager installation finished.
wazuh-manager service started.
Filebeat installation finished.
filebeat service started.
Wazuh dashboard installation finished.
wazuh-dashboard service started.
Installation finished.
```

**Retrieve Admin Password:**

```bash
sudo tar -O -xvf wazuh-install-files.tar wazuh-install-files/wazuh-passwords.txt
```

